(Description)
Given an integer n, return true if it is a power of two. Otherwise, return false.
An integer n is a power of two, if there exists an integer x such that n == 2x.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfTwo(int n) {
        return n > 0 && (n & (n-1)) == 0;
    }
}

--- Approach ---
Bitwise Operator was the key in this algorithm.
Because there was a pattern when the numbers that are power of two.
For example,
- 1 = 0001,
- 2 = 0010,
- 4 = 0100,
- 8 = 1000, ...
=> Only one bit is 1 if the given number is power of 2.

Therefore when n is power of 2, and if n & (n-1) is calculated, the result is always 0.
